******
[4] UK: additional imported cases
Date: Fri 27 May 2011
Source: Daily Mail [edited]
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/health/article-1391526/Cucumber-E-coli-2-people-Britain-diagnosed-5-killed-Germany.html?ITO=1490


Two people have been diagnosed in Britain with the _E. coli_ strain
that has already claimed 5 lives in Germany.

The 2 UK victims are Germans who traveled from their homeland and
fell ill after entering Britain. There is a 3rd suspected case but it
has yet to be confirmed. Although the infection can be passed
person-to-person through hand-to-mouth contact the Health Protection
Agency [HPA] said there was no evidence of any such secondary
infections.

It is understood the suspect salad items have not been sold in the UK
but the HPA said checks are ongoing. They added that the outbreak is
mainly affecting adults, almost 70 per cent of whom are women.

[Byline: Allan Hall]

